$ Experiment: When is JavaScript executed

{ Inline JavaScript

  The following experiment uses a → development/languages/Python → web/webserver[Web Server] that serves a web page very slowly over a period of ca. 10 seconds.

  The experiment demonstrates that (inline) JavaScript is executed as soon as the → development/web/browser[browser] has fetched the closing `</script>` tag.

  gh|about-HTML|/tags/script/when-executed/web-server-inline-script.py||

}

sa:
  The → development/web/HTML/tags/script[`<script>`] tag
